# List of all currently included addons


## [ls-Glass](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/ls-glass)
Nicer chat frame

## [Opie](https://www.townlong-yak.com/addons/opie)
Extremely convenient radial menu addon. Default rings are: F4 for consumables (not yet configured until Dragonflight) F5 for convenience features (hearthstones/banks/teleports/mailboxes/etc) and F6 for the rest of the wormholes/travel, F7 for raid markers.

## [Plater](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/plater-nameplates)
Nameplates.

## [AdvancedInterfaceOptions](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/advancedinterfaceoptions)
Allows easy access to lots of hidden cvars

## [MDT](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/mythic-dungeon-tools)
Mythic+ route planning and viewing tool

## [Handynotes](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/handynotes/)
For all open world content; treasures, rares, dragon glyphs, etc. Only dragonflight packages included by default, but there are plenty useful ones for old content

## [Method Raid Tools](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/method-raid-tools)
Basically MDT but for raiding

## [Unlimited Map Pin Distance](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/unlimited-map-pin-distance)
Makes the blizzard waypoint arrows behave the way they should by default (Ctrl+Click on world map)

## [Xfaction](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/ek-xfaction)
Used for cross faction guild chat

## [MapCoords](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/map-coords)
Just shows cursor coordinates on world map screen

## [Simple Ilvl](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/simple-item-level)
Displays ilvl on items in bags and character frame, I modified to reposition the text and add an exception for the heart of azeroth so don’t update unless it’s broken

## [Nameplate SCT](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/nameplate-scrolling-combat-text)
This is only used for incoming damage, default blizz SCT used for outgoing damage

## [Bigwigs/Littlewigs](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/big-wigs)
Boss mods. Information from this addon is redirected to a vertical timeline WA because I think it presents the information better.
![Pasted image 20221024174138.png](data:image/png;base64,)

## [Bugsack/Grabber](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/bugsack)
LUA bug handler

## [Enhanced Raid Frames](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/enhanced-raid-frames)
Just used to fade the raid frames harder so it’s more obvious when players are out of range. Might have to be customized to 30yd range for evokers.

## [Leatrix Plus](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/leatrix-plus)
handles simple automations and QOL like selling greys among other small things

## [Mouseover Actionbars](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/mouseoveractionbars-mouseover-action-bars)
self explanatory

## SlashWay (homebrew)
Integrates /way XX XX coordinates with the blizzard navigator. no commas

## SlashKB (homebrew)
/kb brings up quickkeybind interface

## FahUI (homebrew)
Enforces some CVars to simplify installation

## [Loot Spec Icon](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/loot-spec-icon)
Sticks a little icon showing your loot spec to the player frame
![Pasted image 20221105133850.png](data:image/png;base64,)

## [MoveAny](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/moveany)
Lets you move, resize, and reset frames that blizzard doesn’t want you to

## [Details](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/details)
DPS meters. For now these have been awkwardly displaced from their usual corner by the unmovable Bagbar and Microbar. 

## [ZigiAuras](https://github.com/glassleo/ZigiAuras)
Gradient database mostly. Only used by the castbar.

## [Clique](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/clique)
![Pasted image 20221023034028.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Mouseover casting for healing and support spells. I encourage you to make your own clique binds, but you should still use my included profiles as a starting point, due to the included macros.

> [!Bug]
> Mouseover keyboard hotkeys (like "C" in the above picture) don't work on the player frame *healthbar* right now. They still work on the 3d portrait ![Pasted image 20221101143919.png](data:image/png;base64,) . They do work on raid/party frames which is what really matters.

## [TellMeWhen](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/tellmewhen)
![Pasted image 20221023032333.png](data:image/png;base64,)
It's this^ thing. It tracks your cooldowns/procs. In the way I use it, the icons are configured and stored in what I call "buckets," and then distributed among Meta-icons around your Personal Resource Display according to certain logic.

> [!Note]
> TMW as I’ve configured it will only track your top trinket (item slot 13) on its display, and only if it’s usable. If you have a usable trinket not worth tracking, put it in the other trinket slot. If you have two on use trinkets worth tracking, I am sorry

# [Weakauras](https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/weakauras-2)
WA is the popular and flexible LUA framework that does a lot of heavy lifting in many UIs. I use this for a lot, but I'll explain a few of the major elements.

### `Procs & Warnings`
![Pasted image 20221023032743.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Maintenance buff type warnings and reminders, mostly.

### `Castbar`
![Pasted image 20221023032948.png](data:image/png;base64,)
![Pasted image 20221023033121.png](data:image/png;base64,)
This fancy castbar basically looks at a giant table to find the "best gradient" for every given spell (not yet fully updated for DF). Features a latency indicator, empowered spell (Evoker thing) support, Uninterruptible cast indicator for PVP.

### `CDFlash`
![Pasted image 20221023033255.png](data:image/png;base64,)
This module near the middle-top of your screen will flash spells for 0.900 seconds as an extra reminder that it's come off cooldown. Some spells are set to not fire here due to how frequently they come off cooldown or other considerations—I’ve gone through them and disabled most short/rotational cooldowns, disable more at your own discretion.

### Aurabars
![Pasted image 20221023033513.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Buff/pet/totem/rarely debuff uptimes. Only **potentially useful** auras are displayed, things that you should actually pay attention to or might theoretically need to actually know the duration of.

### Resources
All class resources such as mana and combo points are handled through Weakauras around the personal nameplate.

### Frame hide
![Pasted image 20221025041808.png](data:image/png;base64,)
This WA bears mentioning: If you’re wondering where this stuff or went or how to get it back, the WA is under Misc WAs, just set it to load never and reload your UI
